{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded", "label": "Port Wrangler \u2014 Code-Grounded Technical Roadmap", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_flyway", "label": "Correction: Liquibase not Flyway", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "liquibase-core is already on the classpath and changesets V1-V4 exist, but spring.liquibase config is commented out and ddl-auto:update is active, causing schema drift between Hibernate-managed entities and V1__init.sql; do not add Flyway \u2014 finish the Liquibase cutover instead: baseline the current schema, enable spring.liquibase, flip ddl-auto to validate."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_springai_version", "label": "Correction: pin Spring AI 1.0.3 GA not 1.0.0-M5", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1.0.0-M5 is a milestone release, which directly violates the hard constraint 'Spring AI 1.0 GA only'; pin 1.0.3, the latest 1.0.x GA patch as of October 2025."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_dbtype_count", "label": "Correction: 26 DbType entries, not 14", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "DbType has 26 entries (databases plus Kafka, RabbitMQ, Conduktor, Grafana, Prometheus, Loki, MinIO, Keycloak, Vault, Nginx, Adminer, pgAdmin), repositioning Port Wrangler as a general local-infra deployer rather than just a DB tool."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_pipeline_exists", "label": "Correction: 4-step deploy pipeline already built", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "ImagePull \u2192 ContainerCreate \u2192 ContainerStart \u2192 Finalise is already built and battle-tested (PipelineOrchestrator, PipelineRunner with @Async execution + post-commit re-fetch, a clean DeployStep SPI); new long-running work like model pulls should reuse the DeployStep SPI, not invent a parallel mechanism."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_mcp_starter_naming", "label": "Correction: spring-ai-starter-mcp-client naming", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "GA renamed all Spring AI MCP starters to the spring-ai-starter-* prefix; use spring-ai-starter-mcp-client, not the old spring-ai-mcp-client-spring-boot-starter naming."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_apple_silicon_gpu", "label": "Correction: Dockerized Ollama on macOS is CPU-only", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "True for native Ollama on macOS but false for Dockerized Ollama \u2014 Docker Desktop on macOS runs a Linux VM with no GPU passthrough, so a containerized Ollama on a Mac runs CPU-only; detect this and warn the user, recommending native Ollama on Mac and containerized on Linux/NVIDIA."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_pgvector_decision", "label": "Vector store decision: pgvector CONFIRM", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "pgvector satisfies the zero-extra-service principle and gives transactional consistency with chat history since the message row and its embedding commit together; Chroma is a second Python service/store, Pinecone is cloud-only, and Weaviate is another container to sync \u2014 all violate zero-extra-service. PostgreSQL 16 is already provisioned by SystemDbProvisioner so pgvector is just a CREATE EXTENSION with no new container or port. pgvector's ANN quality degrades beyond ~1-10M vectors but local-dev scale (tens of thousands of vectors) makes this irrelevant."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_ollama_runtime_decision", "label": "LLM runtime decision: Ollama default + DMR as peer runtime", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Ollama is the right default (OpenAI-compatible API, best Spring AI starter covering both chat and embeddings, broadest model library); Docker Model Runner deserves first-class second-runtime status since it stores models as OCI artifacts and is Compose-native, fitting the 'infra as managed Docker containers' worldview even better than Ollama; LocalAI is relegated to 'community runtime' due to smaller ecosystem and no first-party Spring AI starter."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_embedding_model_decision", "label": "Embedding model decision: nomic-embed-text default", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "768 dims, Apache-2.0, strong quality-per-millisecond on local CPU, runs in the same Ollama already deployed; a pgvector column's dimension is fixed at table creation, so switching embedding models must be an explicit, destructive re-index operation \u2014 never a silent setting."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_springai_10_decision", "label": "AI abstraction decision: Spring AI 1.0 GA pin 1.0.3", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Spring AI 1.0 GA gives ChatClient, ChatMemory/MessageWindowChatMemory/JdbcChatMemoryRepository, the advisor chain, @Tool + ToolCallingManager, PgVectorStore, and an MCP client, all first-party; pinning 1.0.3 satisfies 'GA only' with no ambiguity, and the eventual 1.0.3 to 1.1.x bump is a small migration (mostly the advisor builder API), not a rewrite."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_token_optimization", "label": "Token optimization \u2014 layered context assembly (open-relay pattern)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A bounded verbatim window plus a sub-linearly growing rolling summary plus fixed-k retrieval keeps total prompt tokens flat instead of climbing linearly with conversation length, matching open-relay's reported 30-35% savings at 10 turns and 70-80% at 40+ turns."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_contextassemblyadvisor", "label": "ContextAssemblyAdvisor", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_rollingwindowchatmemory", "label": "RollingWindowChatMemory", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_rollingsummaryservice", "label": "RollingSummaryService (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_memoryretriever", "label": "MemoryRetriever (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_recencyfrequencyscorer", "label": "RecencyFrequencyScorer (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "score = 0.35*semantic + 0.35*recency + 0.30*frequency; pgvector can only sort by vector distance so the pattern is over-fetch by vector (top k*4) then re-rank in Java by the composite score and take top-k."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_tokenbudget", "label": "TokenBudget (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_summarization_trigger", "label": "Hybrid summarization trigger (turns AND tokens)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A single trigger is wrong: 'every N turns' over-summarises short chatty turns and under-summarises long ones, while 'every X tokens' can let turn count drift; use both (SUMMARY_EVERY_N_TURNS=4, VERBATIM_TOKEN_BUDGET=1500), whichever fires first, running as an @Async method after the reply is persisted so the user never waits for compression."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_chatclientconfig", "label": "ChatClientConfig (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelrouter", "label": "ModelRouter (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_ragchatservice", "label": "RagChatService (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_sse_webflux_decision", "label": "SSE via servlet MVC, not WebFlux (design decision)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The app is spring-boot-starter-web (servlet) + JPA; bolting on WebFlux+R2DBC for streaming would double the web stack and fight JPA persistence. Spring MVC can return Flux<ServerSentEvent<...>> directly from a @GetMapping producing TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE and stream over the servlet container's async I/O \u2014 the right call for a memory-conscious local app, avoiding a large risky refactor."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_infrastructuretools", "label": "InfrastructureTools (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Each @Tool method is a thin wrapper over existing services with no new business logic in the tool layer, so the agent executes the same code paths as the UI \u2014 same validation (DeploymentValidations), same pipeline, same recovery \u2014 considered the single most defensible design decision in the roadmap."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_advisor_chain_order", "label": "Advisor chain ordering (Context/RAG before ToolCalling)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "ContextAssemblyAdvisor (order 100) and InfraRagAdvisor (order 200) deliberately sit before the ToolCallingAdvisor (auto-registered last) so the model sees full context when deciding whether to call a tool."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_mempalace_assessment", "label": "MemPalace integration assessment: do not embed", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "MemPalace is a Python process backed by ChromaDB, so embedding it as core would mean a second runtime and a second vector store, violating zero-extra-service; pgvector plus the \u00a73 token-optimization design already covers the memory need at Port Wrangler's scale (infra ops on one machine, not a general personal-memory product with thousands of unrelated conversations). Building the memory system yourself is also a stronger interview story than gluing in a third-party memory service. It is still worth a small opt-in MCP-client hook (gated behind portwrangler.memory.mcp.enabled=false by default) since Port Wrangler can deploy MemPalace like any other managed container."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase0", "label": "Phase 0 \u2014 Hardening (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Renaming the com.dbdeployer Java package to io.portwrangler is tempting but churns all ~85 files and every import; the mitigation is to rename only the product/artifact/repo name and leave the Java package alone since package names are invisible to users and the rename buys nothing but merge pain."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase1", "label": "Phase 1 \u2014 Quick wins + Docker Compose export (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Kafka management was scoped out into a separate dedicated Kafka tool project; Port Wrangler still deploys Kafka but no longer manages it (topic CRUD, consumer-group lag, message browser, Schema Registry), saving roughly 3 weeks and sharpening the product thesis, spent instead on Compose export and Spring config bootstrap quick wins."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_composeexportcontroller", "label": "ComposeExportController", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_composeexportservice", "label": "ComposeExportService", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_connectionstringbuilder", "label": "ConnectionStringBuilder", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase2", "label": "Phase 2 \u2014 LLM Runtime Manager + Model Cookbook (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelruntime_enum", "label": "runtime/ModelRuntime.java (enum: OLLAMA, DOCKER_MODEL_RUNNER)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_gpudetector", "label": "runtime/GpuDetector.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "GPU detection avoids shelling out: inspects Docker via the SDK (docker.infoCmd() runtime presence for NVIDIA), probes device files for AMD (/dev/kfd, /dev/dri), reads OS/arch for Apple Silicon; never runs nvidia-smi from Java on the host, and for in-container confirmation reuses the existing safe argv-array execCapture rather than a shell."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelpullstep", "label": "runtime/ModelPullStep.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_springaisnippetservice", "label": "runtime/SpringAiSnippetService.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_systemprofile", "label": "runtime/SystemProfile.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelcatalog", "label": "runtime/ModelCatalog.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelsuggestionservice", "label": "runtime/ModelSuggestionService.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelcookbookcontroller", "label": "api/ModelCookbookController.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase3", "label": "Phase 3 \u2014 Spring AI foundation + Model Comparison (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_chatcontroller", "label": "api/ChatController.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelcomparisoncontroller", "label": "api/ModelComparisonController.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_modelcomparisonservice", "label": "service/ModelComparisonService.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase4", "label": "Phase 4 \u2014 RAG pipeline (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_ingestionservice", "label": "rag/IngestionService.java (design)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_log_chunking_strategy", "label": "Log chunking strategy (severity into metadata)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Logs are not prose, so chunking splits on log-record boundaries (timestamp-prefixed lines), groups N adjacent records per chunk, and promotes severity (level=ERROR|WARN|INFO) into metadata so retrieval can boost it, with a severity_boost term ensuring ERROR/WARN chunks outrank INFO for the same semantic distance."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase5", "label": "Phase 5 \u2014 Agentic assistant + safety + MCP server (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_confirmation_flow", "label": "Confirmation flow via manual tool execution (design)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The core safety design: read-only tools run automatically while write/destructive tools run only after explicit user approval, achieved via internalToolExecutionEnabled(false) so the app drives the loop instead of letting the advisor auto-execute; classification is read-only (never gated) / writes (confirm) / destructive (confirm with target echoed back)."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_stacksummary_tool", "label": "stackSummary @Tool(returnDirect=true)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Answers 'what's my stack' in one tool call by combining dbInstanceService.listAll() with connectionStringBuilder to return a structured summary of every running instance; the UI surfaces this as a 'Copy as .env' / 'Copy as Spring config' button, reusing existing data fetching with zero new work."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_readonly_mode_flag", "label": "portwrangler.agent.read-only flag", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Strips all non-read ToolCallbacks so write tools simply don't exist in that execution context, rather than existing but being refused \u2014 a stronger safety boundary than a runtime check."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_runaway_loop_guard", "label": "Runaway-loop guard (MAX_TOOL_ROUNDS=6)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Caps tool iterations per turn to guard against a model looping indefinitely on tool calls; surfaces 'agent exceeded tool budget' if the cap is exceeded."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_portwrangler_mcp_server", "label": "Port Wrangler MCP server (design)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Exposes the same InfrastructureTools methods as MCP tools via @McpTool with identical definitions/validation/pipeline to the agent tools (no duplication), letting Cursor/Continue.dev/VS Code Copilot/Claude Desktop call Port Wrangler's infrastructure tools directly from inside the IDE without opening the app; read-only by default, with destructive tools exposed only via portwrangler.mcp.write-enabled=true and binding to localhost only to mitigate risk."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_phase6", "label": "Phase 6 \u2014 Polish & launch (grounded roadmap)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_schema_cutover_plan", "label": "Database schema cutover plan (\u00a77.1)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Today the schema is managed by Hibernate ddl-auto:update with Liquibase present but dormant; vector/AI tables can't be added cleanly on top of update because it fights changesets and silently re-derives columns, so Phase 0 must baseline the current live schema as V5__baseline.sql, enable Liquibase, and flip Hibernate to ddl-auto:validate before any further schema change is made a changeset."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_vector_store_table", "label": "vector_store table (shared, one HNSW index)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "One shared vector_store table for all embeddings (chat messages, deployments, logs, kafka metadata), discriminated by metadata->>'type', is cheaper to maintain than four separate tables and matches Spring AI PgVectorStore's default table shape so the starter can own it; cross-domain isolation comes from the GIN index on metadata rather than separate tables. HNSW is chosen over IVFFlat because IVFFlat needs representative data to train its lists and would build a bad index on an empty fresh-install table, while HNSW has no training step."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_chat_session_table", "label": "chat_session table", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_chat_message_table", "label": "chat_message table", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "chat_message intentionally duplicates content that also lives in SPRING_AI_CHAT_MEMORY: the Spring AI table is the framework-owned verbatim window, while chat_message is the retrievable corpus with scoring signals (access_count, last_seen, seq) \u2014 different layers of the context-assembly design that should not be conflated."}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_model_runtime_table", "label": "model_runtime table", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_pulled_model_table", "label": "pulled_model table", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_readme_launch_plan", "label": "Open-source launch plan (30 days)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_dbinstanceservice", "label": "DbInstanceService", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_systemdbprovisioner", "label": "SystemDbProvisioner", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded", "target": "docs_cgpt_deep_research_report", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded", "target": "docs_deepseek_research", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded", "target": "docs_claude_ai_management_tool", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/port-wrangler-roadmap-grounded.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_correction_flyway", "target": "docs_port_wrangler_roadmap_grounded_schema_cutover_plan", "relation": "rationale_for", "confidence": "EXTRA